  urldate = {2021-09-02},
  abstract = {🔤本研究调查了海面高度异常 (SSHA) 的分布，目的是量化黑潮-亲潮延伸区 (KOER) 中尺度涡流的特征，该区域在水文测量期间经常观察到强烈的中尺度涡流。使用没有平滑的 Okubo-Weiss 参数，在 KOER 中首次检测到反气旋涡流 (AEs) 和气旋涡流 (CEs) 的密集分布，具有足够的时间和空间覆盖范围。他们对 SSHA 总方差的贡献估计约为 50\%。 AE 和 CE 的最高振幅区域位于黑潮延伸（KE）轴线的北侧和南侧，分别代表暖核环和冷核环；这些区域沿着日本和千岛-堪察加海沟向极地延伸，特别是对于 AE。沿亚北极锋 (SAF) 也可识别出双极性涡流和中等振幅涡流。 KE 北部和南部地区的涡旋一般向西传播，平均速率为 1-5 cm s21；那些沿着 468N 以南的沟槽和沿着 SAF 的那些分别以 1-2 和 0.5-1 cm s21 的平均速率向极地传播。由于AEs和CEs在KE南北地区的不对称分布，以及它们沿日本和千岛-堪察加海沟的不对称振幅，这些地区存在显着的涡度、热量和盐度涡通量. This study investigates the distribution of the sea surface height anomaly (SSHA) with the aim of quantifying the characteristics of mesoscale eddies in the Kuroshio{\textendash}Oyashio extension region (KOER), where intense mesoscale eddies are commonly observed during hydrographic surveys. Dense distributions of both anticyclonic eddies (AEs) and cyclonic eddies (CEs) are detected for the first time in KOER with sufficient temporal and spatial coverage, using the Okubo{\textendash}Weiss parameter without smoothing. Their contribution to the total SSHA variance is estimated to be about 50\%. The zones of highest amplitudes are located north and south of the axis of the Kuroshio Extension (KE) for AEs and CEs, which represent warm-core and cold-core rings, respectively; the areas extend poleward along the Japan and Kuril{\textendash}Kamchatka Trenches, especially for AEs. Eddies of both polarities and with moderate amplitudes are also recognized along the Subarctic Front (SAF). Eddies in areas north and south of the KE generally propagate westward, at a mean rate of 1{\textendash}5 cm s21; those along the trenches south of 468N and along the SAF propagate poleward at mean rates of 1{\textendash}2 and 0.5{\textendash}1 cm s21, respectively. Because of the asymmetric distribution of the AEs and CEs in the areas north and south of the KE, and the asymmetric amplitude of them along the Japan and Kuril{\textendash}Kamchatka Trenches, there exist significant eddy fluxes of vorticity, heat, and salinity in these areas.},
