  abstract = {🔤利用近 16 年的卫星高度计海面高度 (SSH) 数据，研究了在稳定和不稳定动态之间振荡的黑潮延伸 (KE) 系统的年代际变化。在 10/1992{\textendash}06/1995 和 01/2002{\textendash}12/2004 的稳定状态期间，KE 急流很强烈，并具有向北的纬向平均路径和明确的南部回流环流。在 07/1995{\textendash}12/2001 和 01/2005{\textendash}现在的不稳定状态期间，KE 射流向东输送减少，流动路径向南。两种动态状态之间的转换是由北太平洋东部与太平洋年代际振荡 (PDO) 或北太平洋环流振荡 (NPGO) 相关的盆地尺度风应力旋度强迫引起的。在正 PDO（或负 NPGO）阶段，加强的阿留申低压通过埃克曼散度在北太平洋东部产生负 SSH 异常。当这些风引起的负 SSH 异常以斜压罗斯贝波的形式向西传播时，它们削弱了纬向 KE 射流并将其路径向南移动。随着它的路径向南推 {\dh} \$ 323N{\TH}，深远的 KE 急流必须越过较浅的沙茨基隆起，产生局部干扰，导致它们随后沿着沙茨基隆起以西的 KE 急流发展。当 PDO (NPGO) 变为其负（正）相时，会发生与上述顺序相反的顺序。在 KE 系统从稳定状态过渡到不稳定状态后，发现增强的涡流相互作用加强了 KE 上游路径上的南部再循环环流和准静止曲流。这种非线性涡流相互作用对于确定观测到的 KE 年代际变率的幅度很重要。 Satellite altimeter sea-surface height (SSH) data of the past 16 years are used to investigate the decadal changes of the Kuroshio Extension (KE) system that oscillated between a stable and an unstable dynamic state. During the stable state of 10/1992{\textendash}06/1995 and 01/2002{\textendash}12/2004, the KE jet was intense and had a northerly zonal mean path and a well-defined southern recirculation gyre. During the unstable state of 07/1995{\textendash}12/2001 and 01/2005{\textendash}present, the KE jet had a reduced eastward transport and a more southerly flow path. Transitions between the two dynamic states are caused by the basinscale wind-stress curl forcing in the eastern North Pacific related to the Pacific decadal oscillations (PDOs) or the North Pacific Gyre Oscillations (NPGOs). During the positive PDO (or negative NPGO) phase, the intensified Aleutian Low generates negative SSH anomalies in the eastern North Pacific through Ekman divergence. As these wind-induced negative SSH anomalies propagate to the west as baroclinic Rossby waves, they weaken the zonal KE jet and shift its path southward. As its path is pushed southward {\dh} \$ 323N{\TH}, the deep-reaching KE jet has to ride over the shallow Shatsky Rise, generating localized disturbances that lead to their subsequent development along the KE jet west of the Shatsky Rise. The sequence opposite to that listed above occurs when the PDO (NPGO) changes to its negative (positive) phase. After the KE system transitions from a stable to unstable state, the enhanced eddy interaction is found to strengthen both the southern recirculation gyre and quasi-stationary meanders along the KE's upstream path. This nonlinear eddy interaction is important in determining the amplitude of the observed decadal KE variability.},
