  urldate = {2023-01-29},
  abstract = {🔤通过考虑两次典型的海洋中尺度涡旋合并事件，研究了两个合并反气旋的最终状态是否比初始状态包含更多能量的长期理论``能量悖论''。结果表明，如果在涡旋围绕中心旋转时考虑相对于质心的轨道 AM，则总质量（体积）、总环流（涡量的面积积分）和总角动量 (AM) 是守恒的合并前的质量。对于地下合并，还应包括在地下涡流上方被泰勒-普劳德曼效应捕获的质量。循环和轨道 AM 的守恒定律在以前的理论研究中都被忽视了。由于合并过程中的融合，总涡动能略有下降。相反，合并后总涡流势能 (EPE) 增加。 EPE 的增加主要是由于在合并前涡流下沉低于原始水平而导致的重力势能 (PE) 损失。这意味着涡流的合并需要将背景引力 PE 转换为 EPE。相反，涡度和熵在合并后因此减少。因此，涡流合并效应表现为反向能量级联中的``大型能量泵''。要注意的是，涡守恒和转换定律取决于物理动力学定律，即使可以在数学模型中提供额外的自由度。 The long-term theoretical ``energy paradox'' of whether the final state of two merging anticyclones contains more energy than the initial state is studied by considering two typical merging events of ocean mesoscale eddies. The results demonstrate that the total mass (volume), total circulation (area integration of vorticity), and total angular momentum (AM) are conserved if the orbital AM relative to the center of mass is taken into account as the eddies rotate around the center of mass before merging. For subsurface merging, the mass trapped by the Taylor{\textendash}Proudman effect above the subsurface eddies should also be included. Both conservation laws of circulation and orbital AM have been overlooked in previous theoretical studies. As a result of fusion during merging, the total eddy kinetic energy decreases slightly. In contrast, the total eddy potential energy (EPE) increases after merging. The increase in EPE is mostly supported by the loss of gravitational potential energy (PE) via eddy sinking below the original level prior to merging. This implies that the merging of eddies requires background gravitational PE to be converted to EPE. In contrast, the vorticity and enstrophy consequently decrease after merging. Thus, the eddy merging effect behaves as a ``large-scale energy pump'' in an inverse energy cascade. It is noted that eddy conservation and conversion laws depend on the laws of physical dynamics, even if additional degrees of freedom can be provided in a mathematical model.},
