  doi = {10.1175/JPO-D-18-0253.1},
  urldate = {2023-07-06},
  abstract = {Abstract                            Numerical simulations suggest that submesoscale turbulence may transform lateral buoyancy gradients into vertical stratification and thus restratify the upper ocean via vertical flow. However, the observational evidence for this restratifying process has been lacking due to the difficulty in measuring such ephemeral phenomena, particularly over periods of months to years. This study presents an annual cycle of the vertical velocity and associated restratification estimated from two nested clusters of meso- and submesoscale-resolving moorings, deployed in a typical midocean area of the northeast Atlantic. Vertical velocities inferred using the nondiffusive density equation are substantially stronger at submesoscales (horizontal scales of 1{\textendash}10 km) than at mesoscales (horizontal scales of 10{\textendash}100 km), with respective root-mean-square values of 38.0 {$\pm$} 6.9 and 22.5 {$\pm$} 3.3 m day               -1               . The largest submesoscale vertical velocities and rates of restratification occur in events of a few days' duration in winter and spring, and extend down to at least 200 m below the mixed layer base. These events commonly coincide with the enhancement of submesoscale lateral buoyancy gradients, which is itself associated with persistent mesoscale frontogenesis. This suggests that mesoscale frontogenesis is a regular precursor of the submesoscale turbulence that restratifies the upper ocean. The upper-ocean restratification induced by submesoscale motions integrated over the annual cycle is comparable in magnitude to the net destratification driven by local atmospheric cooling, indicating that submesoscale flows play a significant role in determining the climatological upper-ocean stratification in the study area.},
  keywords = {/unread},
  annotation = {abstractTranslation: 摘要 数值模拟表明，亚中尺度湍流可能将横向浮力梯度转化为垂直分层，从而通过垂直流使上层海洋重新分层。然而，由于难以测量这种短暂现象，特别是在数月至数年的时间内，这种重新分层过程的观测证据一直缺乏。这项研究提出了垂直速度的年度周期和相关的重新分层，这是根据部署在东北大西洋典型海洋中部区域的两个嵌套的中尺度和亚中尺度解析系泊装置群估计的。使用非扩散密度方程推断的垂直速度在亚介尺度（1-10 km 水平尺度）上明显强于介尺度（10-100 km 水平尺度），各自的均方根值为 38.0 {$\pm$} 6.9 和 22.5 {$\pm$} 3.3 m 天-1 。最大的亚中尺度垂直速度和再层化速率发生在冬季和春季持续几天的事件中，并向下延伸到混合层基底以下至少 200 m。这些事件通常与亚中尺度横向浮力梯度的增强同时发生，而亚中尺度横向浮力梯度本身与持续的中尺度锋生有关。这表明中尺度锋生是使上层海洋重新分层的次中尺度湍流的常规前兆。年循环中亚中尺度运动引起的上层海洋再分层在幅度上与当地大气冷却驱动的净去层化相当，表明亚中尺度流在确定研究区域气候上层海洋分层方面发挥着重要作用。},
