  urldate = {2023-07-05},
  abstract = {Different types of mesoscale eddy dynamics are considered in the paper from the viewpoint of their effect on the plankton (mainly phytoplankton) amount and its taxonomic structure. The eddy structures of all types, including cyclonic, anticyclonic, water-body anticyclonic and frontal ones, as well as the dipole structures, actively affect plankton. Theoretical schemes of the influencing mechanisms, which are illustrated by the examples of such an impact on the plankton in the Black Sea, are examined. The analyzed responses of the marine plankton ecosystems to the eddy dynamics and the scientific literature review unambiguously testify the important role of these processes in formation of biological productivity in the seas and oceans. A cyclonic eddy forms the isopycnals rise (a dome-like bend) in its core both in the thermocline and in the pycno-halocline that elevates nitrocline; it promotes bioproductivity increase. In the center of the anticyclonic eddy, the thermocline and pycno-halocline deepen (deflection) which negatively affects bioproductivity. At the same time, the rise of the isopycnals occurs at the eddy periphery that, on the contrary, contributes to increase in primary production. In contrast to a regular anticyclone, a water-body (or lens-like) eddy induces the water rise in a layer above the depth of the maximum orbital velocity of the eddy, in other words, in its upper part it often acts like a cyclone. Thus, in any eddy there are the areas where the thermocline rises to the surface and, therefore, the prerequisites for the bioproductivity increase are formed. Strong winds not only enhance the effect of the eddies on biota, but can completely change the nature of this impact. When exposed to wind, the intensity of the biogenic elements transport to the photic layer in the cyclones can decrease, whereas in the lens-like anticyclones it can increase. The important point is that the long-living eddies change the influencing mechanisms depending on the stage of their evolution. At last, the eddy structures often promote changing in the dominant phytoplankton species that can significantly alter the flow of organic matter to the bottom and affect the global carbon cycle.},
  keywords = {/unread},
  annotation = {titleTranslation: 中尺度涡动力学对海洋生态系统生物生产力的影响（综述） abstractTranslation: 本文从不同类型的中尺度涡动力学对浮游生物（主要是浮游植物）数量及其分类结构的影响的角度进行了考虑。所有类型的涡流结构，包括气旋、反气旋、水体反气旋和锋面涡流结构以及偶极结构，都会积极影响浮游生物。研究了影响机制的理论方案，并通过对黑海浮游生物的影响的例子进行了说明。海洋浮游生物生态系统对涡流动力学的分析响应和科学文献综述明确证明了这些过程在海洋生物生产力形成中的重要作用。气旋涡流在温跃层和密斜斜层的核心形成等密度上升（圆顶状弯曲），从而提升硝斜层；它促进生物生产力的提高。在反气旋涡流的中心，温跃层和密盐跃层加深（偏转），这对生物生产力产生负面影响。与此同时，等密度的上升发生在涡旋外围，相反，这有助于初级生产力的增加。与常规反气旋相反，水体（或透镜状）涡流会导致水在涡流最大轨道速度深度以上的层中上升，换句话说，在其上部，它通常表现为气旋。因此，在任何涡流中都存在温跃层上升到表面的区域，因此形成了生物生产力提高的先决条件。强风不仅增强了涡流对生物群的影响，而且可以完全改变这种影响的性质。当暴露在风中时，在气旋中输送到光层的生物元素的强度会降低，而在透镜状反气旋中则会增加。重要的一点是，长寿的涡流会根据其演化阶段的不同而改变影响机制。最后，涡流结构通常会促进主要浮游植物物种的变化，从而显着改变有机质向底部的流动并影响全球碳循环。},
