  publisher = {{American Meteorological Society}},
  issn = {0022-3670, 1520-0485},
  doi = {10.1175/JPO-D-21-0013.1},
  urldate = {2023-07-06},
  abstract = {Abstract Encountering of energetic ocean eddies and atmosphere storms makes the winter Kuroshio extension a hotspot for air{\textendash}sea interactions. This second part investigates the regulation of vertical eddy heat transport QT in the winter Kuroshio extension mixed layer by different types of air{\textendash}sea interactions, including the atmosphere synoptic forcing, eddy thermal feedback resulting from eddy-induced surface heat flux anomalies, and eddy current feedback from eddy current's imprint on wind stress. Atmosphere synoptic forcing modulates intraseasonal variation of QT by boosting its component contributed by the turbulent thermal wind balance QTTTW during strong cooling events associated with intense winds. In addition, the magnitude of QT is influenced by the direction of synoptic wind stress primarily via QTTTW, with the latter exhibiting enhancement both in the downfront- and upfront-wind forcing. Enhanced QTTTW by the downfront-wind forcing is attributed to increased turbulent vertical viscosity and front intensity caused by the destabilizing wind-driven Ekman buoyancy flux, whereas interaction of uniform wind stress with smaller turbulent vertical viscosity at the front center than periphery (a so-called internal Ekman pumping) accounts for the increased QTTTW in the upfront-wind forcing. The eddy thermal feedback reduces QT significantly through weakening the fronts. In contrast, the eddy current feedback exerts negligible influences on QT, although it weakens eddy kinetic energy (EKE) evidently. This is due to the much reduced effect of eddy current feedback in damping the fronts compared to EKE and also due to the compensation from Ekman pumping induced by the eddy current feedback.},
  chapter = {Journal of Physical Oceanography},
  langid = {english},
  keywords = {Review},
  annotation = {abstractTranslation: 摘要 高能海洋涡流和大气风暴的相遇使冬季黑潮延伸成为海气相互作用的热点。第二部分研究不同类型的海气相互作用对冬季黑潮延伸混合层垂直涡热传输QT的调节，包括大气天气强迫、涡引起的表面热通量异常引起的涡热反馈以及涡流涡流对风应力印记的反馈。大气天气强迫通过增强与强风相关的强冷却事件期间湍流热风平衡 QTTTW 贡献的分量来调节 QT 的季节内变化。此外，QT 的大小主要通过 QTTTW 受天气风应力方向的影响，后者在前风和前风强迫方面均表现出增强。下锋风强迫增强的 QTTTW 归因于不稳定的风驱动埃克曼浮力通量引起的湍流垂直粘度和锋面强度的增加，而均匀风应力与锋面中心比外围更小的湍流垂直粘度的相互作用（a so-称为内部埃克曼抽水）解释了前风强迫中 QTTTW 的增加。涡流热反馈通过削弱前沿而显着降低 QT。相比之下，涡流反馈虽然明显削弱了涡动能（EKE），但对 QT 的影响可以忽略不计。这是由于与 EKE 相比，涡流反馈对前沿的阻尼作用大大降低，而且还由于涡流反馈引起的 Ekman 泵浦的补偿。},
